## How the requirements map to the code

- **Roles** — `users.role` is `viewer` or `editor` (CHECK-constrained). `editor_required`/`login_required` decorators guard the routes; viewers get a 403 on create/edit/restore.
- **Revisions** — every create and edit does an `INSERT` into `revisions` (never an `UPDATE` of content). The "current" version is simply the highest-id revision for a page.
- **View & restore** — `/wiki/<slug>/history` lists all revisions; `/wiki/<slug>/revision/<id>` views one; restore inserts a **new** revision copying the old content, so history is never lost.
- **Editor-only pages** — `pages.editor_only` flag; such pages are filtered from the index and return 403 to viewers on the page/history/revision routes.
- **SQLite** — `wiki.db`, auto-created and seeded with `editor/editor` and `viewer/viewer` on first run.
- **Port 5077** — `app.run(host="127.0.0.1", port=5077)`.

