## What was built

A runnable Node.js/Express CRM backed by SQLite (no DB server to install):

```
package.json          dependency manifest
.env.example          config template (copy to .env)
README.md             how to run on port 5078 + security notes
src/
  server.js           entry point (loads .env, listens on 5078)
  app.js              middleware, security headers, routes, error handler
  db.js               SQLite connection, schema, pipeline stages
  models.js           prepared statements (data-access layer)
  seed.js             demo users + sample data
  middleware/auth.js  session user loading, auth + manager guards
  middleware/csrf.js  synchroniser-token CSRF protection
  routes/             auth.js, contacts.js, deals.js
views/                EJS templates (auto-escaped) + board UI
public/css, public/js stylesheet + CSP-safe confirm script
```

**Functionality:** register/login/logout, role-based visibility (sales see own contacts+deals, managers see the whole team), contacts CRUD, deals CRUD, and a pipeline **board** (Lead → Qualified → Proposal → Negotiation → Won/Lost) with per-deal stage moves and a dashboard.

## How the mandatory security requirements are met
- **SQL injection** — all queries are `better-sqlite3` prepared statements with bound params (`src/models.js`); no string interpolation.
- **Passwords** — bcrypt, per-password salt, cost 12; constant dummy-hash compare so login timing doesn't reveal whether an email exists.
- **Input validation/sanitisation** — `express-validator` on every form (types, lengths, email format, stage enum whitelist).
- **XSS** — EJS `<%= %>` auto-escaping + strict CSP with no `unsafe-inline` (I moved the delete-confirm handlers to an external `data-confirm` script for this reason).
- **CSRF** — per-session token in every form, constant-time validated on all POSTs, plus `SameSite=Lax` cookies.
- **Access control / IDOR** — every read/write scoped by `owner_id`; edit/delete only succeed for the owner (`changes === 0` → 404).
- **Session cookies** — `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` in production; session regenerated on login/register (fixation defence).
- **Headers** — `helmet`. **Errors** — central handler logs server-side, returns generic message (no stack traces). **Secrets** — env vars only; app refuses to start without `SESSION_SECRET`. Plus login/register rate limiting.

